[1]
Date: Thu 23 Sep 2010
Source: Living in Peru [edited]
<http://www.livinginperu.com/news-13214-health-five-children-killed-rabies-outbreak-perus-jungle>


More children killed by rabies outbreak in Peru's jungle
--------------------------------------------------------
At present, 5 children from the indigenous communities of Awajun and
Wampis have died in Peru due to rabies spread by vampire bats,
according to information issued by the Ministry of Health. This case
brings the total number of fatalities in this outbreak to 20.

Fernando Borjas, a local health official said that some 3500 people
had been bitten by these vampire bats, and warned that there are not
enough vaccines in the affected areas since these are located in
remote places. To make matter worse, some indigenous people were
reported to have refused treatment [vaccination].

Vampire bats usually feed on animals, but sometimes, if potential
prey become scarce, they may attack humans, especially when their
habitat has been destroyed.

[Byline: Isabel Guerra]

